summary:
jonerys week, missing moment #1: weapons training
“You need to widen your stance,” Jon says. He’s managed to block her, again....
caption:
jonerys week, missing moment #1: weapons training

“You need to widen your stance,” Jon says. He’s managed to block her, again. It isn’t difficult. She broadcasts every move she makes, rookie that she is. Daenerys has her brow driven upwards into a smile, exertion written on her face.

He returns the gesture before pulling his wooden sword back, then slamming it into hers, knocking her off balance. As her own sword clatters against the ship’s floor, he moves behind her. “Here. Let me show you again.”

they’re about to have the most ridiculous fight of their lives against an army of 100,000+ zombies… I think Jon can show the lady how to handle a sword before the fighting begins lol

but hello. I didn’t really have anything for any of the actual prompts this week cause I’m idk both boring and incapable of imaginative thought so I instead will post one moment that ought to have been in the show every day this week. this and the next are pretty out there, but the last five will at least fulfill the actual prompts. I wasn’t gonna post them til day 4 but since the tag is pretty uninhabited (no judgment - rip our hopes and dreams 2k19) I’m just doin it anyways. don’t mind me~ happy shipping everyone 😭

summary: It is not lost on me that in Daenerys III in A Game of Thrones, after being physically and emotionally put down by Viserys, Dany...
body:
It is not lost on me that in Daenerys III in A Game of Thrones, after being physically and emotionally put down by Viserys, Dany seeks comfort from one of her dragons eggs. It is specifically the green one, which would eventually become Rhaegal named after her brother Rhaegar.

Therefore, after being emotionally abused by one brother, Dany sought comfort in her other brother Rhaegar and that is so sad and beautiful.

And this line “she was lying there, holding the egg, when she felt the child move within in her…as if he were reaching out, brother to brother, blood to blood.”

summary: The funny thing is that the absolute idiots behind Game of Thrones didn't even decide whether they wanted to make Daenerys mad...
body:
The funny thing is that the absolute idiots behind Game of Thrones didn’t even decide whether they wanted to make Daenerys mad or evil, they just clumsily shoved both tropes on her and expected the result to make any sort of sense, even when one contradicts the other.

In 8x05 they have the whole ~dark~ “let it be fear” bit after Lady Macbeth is denied sex by the male hero, and ten minutes later in the inside the episode D&D claim the burning of King’s Landing was an instantaneous decision. That Dany just went heard the bells or saw the red keep or whatever and oooops! She went nuts at the snap of a finger.

For fuck’s sake, at least pick a narrative and stick to it.

You want to make Daenerys into an Evil Queen that rules with fear (a completely logical response to a bunch of Jon Snow’s buddies kissing his ass, and a plausible reason for a woman that has gone through fucking hell and back more times than I can count to fall into Despair™ because it somehow means that My People Will Never Love Me)? Cool. It’s a good thing she’s got a full grown dragon with her, since it ticks the instill-fear-on-subjects prerequisite already. Executing any potential threats to the throne (like, I don’t know, Jon Snow) would be the logical next step for such a character, making sure they’re the undisputable heir and all.

You want to turn her into Aerys 2.0 for some unfathomable reason? Well then you can’t possibly expect me to believe that Daenerys would be alone in a room with the guy that challenges her claim to the throne for more than five seconds, let alone carelessly sharing childhood memories and relinquishing her power to him and suggesting that they rule together. Where’s the madness you claimed overtook her to the point of committing a freaking genocide not an hour ago? Does it come with an on/off button or something? Where’s the paranoia? Where’s seeing enemies and people conspiring against you everywhere like Aerys did, especially since, in Dany’s case it’s not even paranoia but reality?

MAKE. YOUR. IDIOTIC. PLOT. MAKE. SENSE. FOR. MORE. THAN. FIVE. CONSECUTIVE. MINUTES. YOU. BLITHERING. IDIOTS.
